main event: A pilot from Eastern Airlines Flight 883 observed a bright object traveling in a south-southwesterly direction at a high rate of speed for approximately 70 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on November 30, 1953, at 2125 Zulu time., The location of the sighting was in the Atlantic Ocean at coordinates 39-27N 55-14W., The object was traveling at a high rate of speed., The pilot reported no physical evidence found., The conclusion of the report categorized the object as unidentified.
sighted object: a bright object in the sky
